Incoming Manchester United manager Erik ten Hag has wasted no time in commencing preparations for his summer arrival. Ten Hag has held a recruitment meeting with United in Amsterdam the day after guiding Ajax to their third Dutch Eredivisie title of his tenure. ESPN report the Dutchman is trying to get a head start with his new job at Old Trafford after lifting his latest piece of silverware with Ajax. On Thursday, has met United representatives to discuss the club's summer recruitment, including the potential ins and outs in his first transfer window as boss. Ten Hag is expected to oversee the start of a significant rebuild at United ahead of his first season in charge, with several first-team players expected to depart. Lee Grant, Nemanja Matic, Paul Pogba, Juan Mata, Jesse Lingard and Edinson Cavani will all leave on free transfers. Aaron Wan-Bissaka, Phil Jones, Eric Bailly, Axel Tuanzebe and Anthony Martial are other names who face increasingly uncertain futures at the club. And with a mass exodus, new signings will follow, and that will have been one of the topics of Ten Hag's meeting in the Dutch capital. JUST IN: Liverpool fired Klopp warning as Reds advised to 'move on' from Salah  We'll be bringing you the very latest updates, pictures, and video on this breaking news story. For the latest news and breaking news visit:https://www.express.co.uk/sportStay up to date with all the big headlines, pictures, analysis, opinion, and video on the stories that matter to you.Follow us on Twitter @DExpress_Sport - the official Daily Express & Express.co.uk Twitter account - providing real news in real-time.We're also on Facebook @DailyExpressSport - offering your must-see news, features, videos, and pictures throughout the day to like, comment, and share from the Daily Express, Sunday Express, and Express.co.uk.